---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="ToolPolaris - AI Tool Rankings for Marketing Professionals"
  description="ToolPolaris cuts through 3,000+ AI tools to give marketing professionals honest, role-specific rankings. No hype. Find the stack that actually fits how you work."
>
  <script
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify({
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@graph': [
        {
          '@type': 'Organization',
          '@id': 'https://toolpolaris.com/#organization',
          name: 'ToolPolaris',
          url: 'https://toolpolaris.com',
          logo: {
            '@type': 'ImageObject',
            url: 'https://toolpolaris.com/toolpolaris-logo-300.png'
          }
        },
        {
          '@type': 'WebSite',
          '@id': 'https://toolpolaris.com/#website',
          url: 'https://toolpolaris.com',
          name: 'ToolPolaris',
          publisher: { '@id': 'https://toolpolaris.com/#organization' },
          potentialAction: {
            '@type': 'SearchAction',
            target: 'https://toolpolaris.com/tools/?q={search_term_string}',
            'query-input': 'required name=search_term_string'
          }
        }
      ]
    })}
  />

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-star" aria-hidden="true">★</div>
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow">AI Tools for Marketing Professionals</div>
        <h1>
          Stop wasting hours on AI tools that do not fit
          <em>how marketers actually work.</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="sub">
          ToolPolaris cuts through 3,000+ AI tools to give marketing professionals honest,
          role-specific rankings so you can build a stack that makes you faster without
          the trial-and-error tax.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta-group">
          <a href="/categories/" class="btn-primary">Get AI Tool Recommendations &rarr;</a>
          <a href="/tools/" class="btn-secondary">Browse All Tools</a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-micro">Free to use · No signup required · Updated weekly</p>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-panel surface-card">
        <div class="hero-panel-head">
          <span class="hero-panel-kicker">✦ This week on ToolPolaris</span>
          <span class="hero-panel-badge">Editorial-first</span>
        </div>
        <h2>What you get instead of another generic AI tools list</h2>
        <ul class="hero-panel-list">
          <li>Role-specific recommendations for content, SEO, paid media, social, and ops.</li>
          <li>Clear tradeoffs on pricing, workflow fit, and where a tool falls short.</li>
          <li>Weekly updates when launches or pricing changes actually matter.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="container trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> 200+ tools reviewed</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> 40+ marketing use cases</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> Updated weekly</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> Editorial-first rankings</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Why ToolPolaris</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Recommendations that actually fit how you do your job</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Generic "best AI tools" lists are written for everyone, which means they are optimized for no one.</p>
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit-card surface-card">
          <div class="benefit-icon">🎯</div>
          <h3>Rankings built around your role, not everyone else's</h3>
          <p>A content marketer, a paid media manager, and a marketing ops lead have different workflows. ToolPolaris gives each of them different recommendations because the right tool depends on how you actually spend your day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card surface-card">
          <div class="benefit-icon">🔍</div>
          <h3>We tell you what the tool actually does and does not do</h3>
          <p>Every tool has a homepage that makes it sound transformational. We test against real marketing workflows and give you the honest read: what it is genuinely good at, where it falls short, and whether the price is worth it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card surface-card">
          <div class="benefit-icon">🔄</div>
          <h3>Kept current as the landscape shifts</h3>
          <p>A tool that was best-in-class six months ago may have been leapfrogged or had its pricing restructured. We track the space continuously and update rankings when something meaningful changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Browse by Use Case</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Find tools for your specific workflow</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Pick the use case closest to what you actually need, not a broad category that covers everything.</p>
      <div class="categories-grid">
        <a href="/tools/ai-writing-tools-marketers/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">✍️</span> AI Writing</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-social-media-marketing-tools/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">📱</span> Social Media</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-seo-tools-marketers/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">🔎</span> SEO &amp; Content</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-ad-copy-tools/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">📣</span> Ad Copy</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-tools-for-market-research/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">🧠</span> Market Research</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-automation-tools-marketers/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">⚡</span> Automation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">What Marketers Say</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Finally, rankings you can trust</h2>
      <div class="testimonials-grid">
        <div class="testimonial surface-card">
          <p>"I've bookmarked a lot of AI tool sites. ToolPolaris is the first one where I actually trust the rankings are not just whoever paid the most."</p>
          <div class="testimonial-author">Rachel M. · Marketing Manager, SaaS</div>
        </div>
        <div class="testimonial surface-card">
          <p>"Finally found a solid AI writing tool recommendation that accounted for the fact that I'm writing B2B technical content, not generic blog posts."</p>
          <div class="testimonial-author">James T. · Content Strategist, B2B Tech</div>
        </div>
        <div class="testimonial surface-card">
          <p>"Saved me at least three bad software subscriptions this quarter. The 'not worth it' verdicts are just as valuable as the recommendations."</p>
          <div class="testimonial-author">Priya S. · Head of Marketing, Ecommerce</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" id="newsletter">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to stop guessing and build a stack that actually works?</h2>
      <p>Browse role-specific AI tool rankings. Free, no signup required.</p>
      <a href="/tools/" class="btn-primary cta-button">Browse All Tool Reviews &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container faq-shell">
      <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Good questions we get a lot</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <details>
            <summary>How does ToolPolaris make money?</summary>
            <p>We earn affiliate commissions when you sign up for a tool through one of our links. This is disclosed clearly on every page. Our rankings are editorial-first because long-term trust matters more than steering you toward the highest-paying partner.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <details>
            <summary>Are your rankings based on actual testing or just aggregated specs?</summary>
            <p>Every featured tool is evaluated against real marketing workflows, not spec sheets. We assess the tasks marketers actually use them for: writing, campaign planning, performance analysis, reporting, and automation.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <details>
            <summary>How often are rankings updated?</summary>
            <p>We review rankings monthly and publish updates whenever a tool releases a meaningful change, raises or cuts pricing, or a new competitor enters a category.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <details>
            <summary>Why trust this over G2, Capterra, or Product Hunt?</summary>
            <p>G2 and Capterra aggregate user reviews, which can be useful but noisy and not filtered by profession or use case. ToolPolaris gives you editorial rankings built specifically around marketing workflows.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <details>
            <summary>Can I request a tool review or suggest a category you're missing?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Use the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a> and tell us what you want covered. We prioritize review requests from readers because that shows us what the market actually needs.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--brand-dark);
    padding: 96px 0 80px;
  }

  .hero-star {
    position: absolute;
    top: -56px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    font-size: 340px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--brand-accent);
    opacity: 0.03;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.5fr) minmax(300px, 0.9fr);
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: end;
  }

  .hero-copy {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.15);
    color: var(--brand-accent);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1.2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.3rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.6px;
    color: var(--color-white);
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }

  .hero h1 em {
    display: block;
    color: var(--brand-accent);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .hero p.sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.15rem);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-cta-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hero-micro {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.44);
    margin-top: 16px;
  }

  .hero-panel {
    padding: 24px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.96);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
  }

  .hero-panel:hover {
    transform: none;
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22);
  }

  .hero-panel-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .hero-panel-kicker {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1.2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--brand-accent);
  }

  .hero-panel-badge {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    background: var(--brand-light);
    padding: 6px 10px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
  }

  .hero-panel h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .hero-panel-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .hero-panel-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 18px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .hero-panel-list li::before {
    content: '✦';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--brand-accent);
  }

  .trust-bar {
    background: var(--color-white);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    padding: 18px 0;
  }

  .trust-bar-inner {
    display: flex;
    gap: 32px;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .trust-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .star {
    color: var(--brand-accent);
  }

  .benefits-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 28px;
    margin-top: 52px;
  }

  .benefit-card {
    padding: 32px 28px;
  }

  .benefit-icon {
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    background: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.12);
    border-radius: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .benefit-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .benefit-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .categories-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 44px;
  }

  .category-pill {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 14px 18px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: var(--transition-color), box-shadow 200ms ease;
  }

  .category-pill:hover {
    border-color: var(--brand-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.12);
  }

  .emoji {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .testimonials-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 24px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .testimonial {
    position: relative;
    padding: 28px 26px;
  }

  .testimonial::before {
    content: '"';
    position: absolute;
    top: 16px;
    left: 22px;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--brand-accent);
    opacity: 0.4;
    font-family: Georgia, serif;
  }

  .testimonial p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .testimonial-author {
    margin-top: 18px;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .cta-button {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    padding: 16px 32px;
  }

  .faq-shell {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .faq-list {
    margin-top: 44px;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    padding: 22px 0;
  }

  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
  }

  details summary {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  details summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--brand-accent);
    transition: transform 200ms ease;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  details[open] summary::after {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  details p {
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  details a {
    color: var(--brand-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  details a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
    }

    .hero-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 72px 0 56px;
    }

    .hero h1 em {
      display: inline;
    }

    .hero-panel-head {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
